title: Cant see prices anymore

author: April Woods
comment: I like that this app is easy to use. I can plan my entire grocery list plus corresponding coupons and then when im at the store i just swipe my frys card and the savings are instantly applied. Sure beats clipping coupons

author: connie k
comment: I love using the app and getting the extra savings but it only holds 149 coupons in my coupons.... And then it just errors if you try to add more

author: Jolina Morris
comment: This app sucks. Half the coupons that are listed in the add aren't available when searched. You can't just select a certain category to use. The Safeway app is way better.

author: Jason Hallock
comment: Good to have on the go. Even go on coupons.

author: Brett Latin
comment: Drains my phone battery Fast
I'm  not sure yet

author: Kathy Kennedy
comment: I've been a customer for 36 yrs.  I love how your stores are laid out.  The only thing I don't like is, your gas points are only good for a month.  I don't think they should expire.  I spend approx $1200 a month and you have to spend $1000 to get $1.00 off for gas.  I feel I have earned those points and should be able to keep them.  Maybe you can change your policy to no more than $1.00 off a gallon at one time.  Thank for allowing me to give my opinion.

author: mike dillon
comment: Garbage app. Let's me log in, but doesn't link to my card. When I try to link it, it tells me it doesn't exist. When I try to create a new card, it tells me my name or ID is invalid.  So I make an entirely new account with my business email. Same damn problem. Then I go to the website, and it locks me out the very first time I try to link my card, saying I've attempted to unsuccessfully log in more than 5 times and locks everything.

author: Melabor Sarasvati
comment: Coupon feature no longer works,  it says it is experiencing technical difficulties. I have uninstalled and reinstalled app.  I have signed out and back in,  still nothing.  Features work on website however.  Please fix app coupon feature.  Thanks.

author: Walter Howard
comment: 2 major issues. It won't filter either the 5x Simple Truth coupons, nor the Click List only ones, even though I have them unchecked. Also shows me items that aren't carried at my local store, and can't tell me what aisle coupon items are in.

author: Dianne Meyers
comment: Frustrating to use because it seems to limit ability to add coupons.  I like to add all coupons before I shop but it consistently fails after adding some and gives a technical difficulties message.

author: M3 Money
comment: My pharmacy is with Fry's, ii use to be able to submit for refills using this app.  But it stopped working correctly somebody fix it!

author: Nicole Dambrosio
comment: The app won't allow me to load coupons anymore. Those coupons help allot. I usually only shop at frys but I'm going to have to find a new store that keeps up on their things and fixes problems. They even built a new frys across the street from the original one where I live and honestly the employees are rude and now the app issues...just more reason I don't wanna go there and shop anymore...

Liked the original, not liking the updated version. It's also more work to get coupons when using a grocery list verses the "click list".
